text: Park Hye-mi is a South Korean taekwondo practitioner. She won a silver medal in lightweight at the 2007 World Taekwondo Championships, after being defeated by Karine Sergerie in the final. She won a gold medal at the 2008 Asian Taekwondo Championships. She participated in welterweight at the 2009 World Taekwondo Championships, where she was defeated by eventual gold medalist Gwladys Épangue at an early stage. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Living people Category:South Korean female taekwondo practitioners Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists Category:Asian Taekwondo Championships medalists
